      "blocks": {
        "q1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What does Davines Energizing Shampoo do for thinning hair?",
            "content": "<p>It gently cleanses while micro-stimulating the scalp to encourage fuller, faster-looking growth and to thicken the hair you already have. It’s part of the Naturaltech line that targets specific scalp and hair concerns.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Will it regrow hair where it’s already gone?",
            "content": "<p>No. It won’t grow hair back on areas that are completely bare (shiny), but it helps thicken and strengthen existing hair and supports a healthier growth environment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is it sulfate-free and suitable for daily use?",
            "content": "<p>It’s free of harsh sulfates (SLS/SLES) and parabens and is plant-based — but it’s a targeted treatment shampoo, not a daily one, so it isn’t advised for daily use. The most frequent recommended use is every other day; see the usage guide below for the full schedule.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q4": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I use the Davines Naturaltech Energizing Shampoo, and how often should I use it?",
            "content": "<p>Gently massage about a tablespoon of the shampoo into damp hair, leave it on for 2 to 3 minutes, and rinse thoroughly. Repeat the application if necessary. For best results, alternate its use with the Davines Renewing Shampoo or Well-Being Shampoo.</p><p>Frequency of Use:</p><p>Intensive treatment: Use every other day for 1 month.</p><p>Maintenance treatment: Use twice a week for 2 months.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
